Acer, Kumho, Philippine Seven: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-07-21T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/acer-kumho-philippine-seven-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT): The world’s second-largest supplier of
 notebook computers  agreed to buy U.S.-based iGware Inc. for $320
million to upgrade its cloud-computing technology. Acer may also
pay $75 million as performance-based compensation, Taipei-based
Acer said in a statement. Separately, Acer will return to profit
this quarter after a loss for the second quarter, according to
chairman and chief executive officer J.T. Wang. Acer gained 3.6
percent to NT$41.35.  China Shenhua Energy Co. (1088 HK): China Shenhua’s
commercial coal production in June rose 40 percent from a year
earlier to 24.8 million tons, the company said in a statement to
the Hong Kong stock exchange. Sales increased 25 percent to 32.8
million tons in June, the company said. The stock added 0.5
percent to HK$38.80.  Kumho Industrial Co. (002990 KS): Kumho is discussions with
creditors to improve its financials. The talks include selling
its stake in Daewoo Engineering & Construction Co., Kumho said
in a regulatory filing. Kumho rose 4 percent to 9,450 won.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net . 